\begin{abstract}
We introduce and study Choquet-Monge-Amp\`ere classes on compact K\"ahler manifolds.
They consist of quasi-plurisubharmonic functions whose sublevel sets have
small enough asymptotic Monge-Amp\`ere capacity.
We compare them with  finite energy classes, which have recently played an important
role in  K\"ahler Geometry.
\end{abstract}


