\section*{Introduction}



Let $(X,\omega)$ be a compact K\"ahler manifold of complex dimension $n \geq 1$.
Recall that a quasi-plurisubharmonic function (qpsh for short) on $X$ is
an upper semi-continuous function ${\varphi}:X \rightarrow {\mathbb{R}} \cup \{-\infty\}$
which is locally the sum of a plurisubharmonic and a smooth function.
We write ${\varphi} \in PSH(X,\omega)$ if ${\varphi}$ is qpsh and
$\omega_{\varphi}:=\omega+dd^c {\varphi}$ is a positive current.
Here $d=\partial+\overline{\partial}$ and $d^c =\frac{i}{2\pi}(\partial-\overline{\partial})$
are both real operators, so that $dd^c=\frac{i}{\pi} \partial\overline{\partial}$.

